-- EBRD, Erste Bank Croatia Lend 40 Million Euros to Local Firms
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-12-10T13:04:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-10/ebrd-erste-bank-croatia-lend-40-million-euros-to-local-firms.html
Erste & Steiermaerkische Bank d.d.,
a unit of  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS) , and the  European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development  will lend 40 million euros ($51
million) to small business and individual customers in  Croatia .  The funds will be channeled to small- and medium-sized
enterprises through investment loans and working capital
facilities to enhance their competitiveness as Croatia get ready
to join the European Union in July, the two banks said today in
a joint e-mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  